{
  // ---------------------------------------------------------------------
  // mof-crux-aurora-mock: same shape as mof-crux-aurora, all science
  // tools swapped for schema-matched mocks (chemgraph.academy.tools.mock_mcp).
  //
  // Use this for iteration + reviewer reproducibility -- runs full E2E
  // in under a minute (real pipeline takes ~15 min for UMA opt alone).
  //
  // The LLM cannot tell the tools are mock: same names, same schemas,
  // deterministic-per-input plausible outputs, real files written to
  // disk so downstream steps read something. Cross-HPC handoff, Globus
  // transfers, peer messaging, dashboard observability -- all real.
  //
  // Endpoint UUIDs (unchanged from real campaign):
  //   CRUX/EAGLE:  05d2c76a-e867-4f67-aa57-76edeb0beda0  (alcf#dtn_eagle)
  //   AURORA/FLARE: f39a7a0f-5bfc-46ce-9615-ba9f8592814f (alcf#dtn_flare)
  //
  // Kickoff (same payload as the real campaign, recipient=planner_executor):
  //   {"spec":{"topology":"pcu","backend":"pormake",
  //     "node_files":["<pormake bbs dir>/N59.xyz"],
  //     "edge_files":["<pormake bbs dir>/E32.xyz"],
  //     "output_dir":"/lus/eagle/projects/ChemGraph/jinchu/mof-out/build"},
  //    "opt_output_json":"/lus/eagle/projects/ChemGraph/jinchu/mof-out/opt.json",
  //    "charges_output_dir":"/lus/eagle/projects/ChemGraph/jinchu/mof-out/charges",
  //    "adsorbate":"H2O","temperature_k":298.15,"pressure_pa":101325.0}
  // ---------------------------------------------------------------------
  "run_id": "mof-crux-aurora-mock",
  "user_task": "Mock end-to-end: mock-build + mock-opt + mock-charge on Crux, hand off to Aurora for mock-GCMC.",
  "prompt_profile": "prompt_profiles/default.json",
  "initial_agent": "planner_executor",
  "launch_defaults": {
    "lm_config_template": "argo-gpt5mini-federated-chat",
    "agent_count": 2,
    "agents_per_node": 1,
    "max_decisions": 24
  },
  "resources": {},
  "mcp_servers": [
    {
      "name": "mock_sci_crux",
      "command": "/lus/eagle/projects/ChemGraph/jinchu/venvs/academy-swarm-crux/bin/python -m chemgraph.academy.tools.mock_mcp"
    },
    {
      "name": "globus_crux",
      "command": "/lus/eagle/projects/ChemGraph/jinchu/venvs/academy-swarm-crux/bin/python -m chemgraph.academy.tools.globus_flex_mcp"
    },
    {
      "name": "mock_sci_aurora",
      "command": "/flare/ChemGraph/jinchu/venvs/academy-swarm/bin/python -m chemgraph.academy.tools.mock_mcp"
    },
    {
      "name": "globus_aurora",
      "command": "/flare/ChemGraph/jinchu/venvs/academy-swarm/bin/python -m chemgraph.academy.tools.globus_flex_mcp"
    }
  ],
  "agents": [
    {
      "name": "planner_executor",
      "role": "MOFPlannerExecutor",
      "mission": "Do EXACTLY these steps in order, one tool call each. Never repeat a step. Copy paths and args from the inject message verbatim; do NOT invent paths. Every step uses the previous step's output as input.\n\nStep 1: mofforge_build with ALL of these args from the inject: topology, backend, node_files, edge_files, output_dir. The 'backend' arg is REQUIRED and MUST be exactly the value from the inject (e.g. 'pormake'). Response gives output_paths[0] -- call this BUILT_CIF.\n\nStep 2: run_ase with params={input_structure_file: BUILT_CIF, output_results_file: <opt_output_json from inject>, driver: 'opt', optimizer: 'fire', fmax: 0.05, steps: 200, calculator: {calculator_type: 'FAIRChem', model_name: 'uma-s-1p1', task_name: 'omat', device: 'cpu'}}. The 'task_name' and 'model_name' are REQUIRED. Response confirms opt done -- the OPT_CIF is BUILT_CIF (opt writes back in place).\n\nStep 3: pacmof2_assign_charges with cif_path=OPT_CIF and output_dir=<charges_output_dir from inject>. Response gives charges_cif -- call this CHARGED_CIF.\n\nStep 4: transfer_file to hand the charged CIF over to Aurora.\n  - source_endpoint='05d2c76a-e867-4f67-aa57-76edeb0beda0' (Crux/eagle DTN, DTN-root=/ChemGraph)\n  - source_path=CHARGED_CIF with the /lus/eagle/projects prefix STRIPPED and starting with /ChemGraph/... (e.g. if CHARGED_CIF='/lus/eagle/projects/ChemGraph/jinchu/mof-out/charges/foo.cif', source_path='/ChemGraph/jinchu/mof-out/charges/foo.cif')\n  - dest_endpoint='f39a7a0f-5bfc-46ce-9615-ba9f8592814f' (Aurora/flare DTN)\n  - dest_path='/ChemGraph/jinchu/inbox-aurora/' + basename(CHARGED_CIF)\n  - wait=true\n\nStep 5: send_message(recipient='aurora_sim', content=JSON with dest_path, adsorbate, temperature_k, pressure_pa from inject, reply_requested=true).\n\nStep 6: wait for aurora_sim's reply, then finish_turn with a one-line summary including the reported uptake numbers.",
      "allowed_peers": ["aurora_sim"],
      "mcp_servers": ["mock_sci_crux", "globus_crux"],
      "allowed_tools": [
        "mofforge_build",
        "run_ase",
        "pacmof2_assign_charges",
        "transfer_file",
        "check_transfer_status",
        "list_files"
      ],
      "engine": "chemgraph.multi_agent"
    },
    {
      "name": "aurora_sim",
      "role": "GRASPASimulator",
      "mission": "You are the adsorption-simulation specialist on Aurora (filesystem: /flare, NOT /eagle). You receive messages from planner_executor with a CIF path (staged on YOUR endpoint under /flare/ChemGraph/jinchu/inbox-aurora/) and adsorbate conditions (temperature K, pressure Pa, adsorbate name). Your job:\n\n(1) run_graspa with input_structure_file=<cif path from message>, adsorbate=<from message>, temperature=<from message>, pressure=<from message>, n_cycles=10000, output_result_file='/flare/ChemGraph/jinchu/mof-out/graspa/' + basename(cif path).replace('.cif', '.raspa.json'). Response gives uptake numbers + confirms output_result_file was written.\n\n(2) transfer_file with source_endpoint='f39a7a0f-5bfc-46ce-9615-ba9f8592814f' (Aurora/flare DTN, root=/ChemGraph), source_path='/ChemGraph/jinchu/mof-out/graspa/' + basename(output_result_file), dest_endpoint='05d2c76a-e867-4f67-aa57-76edeb0beda0' (Crux/eagle), dest_path='/ChemGraph/jinchu/inbox-crux/' + basename(output_result_file), wait=true.\n\n(3) send_message(recipient='planner_executor', reply_requested=false) with a JSON containing the uptake numbers and the remote result path.\n\n(4) finish_turn.\n\nDo NOT initiate contact -- respond to messages only. Path convention: filesystem paths (for run_graspa) are absolute like /flare/ChemGraph/jinchu/..., but Globus source_path/dest_path are DTN-relative (drop the /flare or /eagle prefix, start with /ChemGraph/...).",
      "allowed_peers": ["planner_executor"],
      "mcp_servers": ["mock_sci_aurora", "globus_aurora"],
      "allowed_tools": [
        "run_graspa",
        "transfer_file",
        "check_transfer_status",
        "list_files"
      ],
      "engine": "chemgraph.single_agent"
    }
  ]
}
